<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <i>New York Times</i>. "Bomb For Herrick Wounds His Valet In His Paris Home." October 19, 1921: "The infernal machine [bomb] is believed by the Paris police to have been the work of French Communists, who for the last two weeks have been conducting a campaign against the execution of two Italians, Sacco and Vanzetti." Years later, the sender of the bomb was revealed to be May Picqueray (1893-1983), a militant anarchist and editor of <i>Le Réfractaire</i>.</li>
